Stir grits slowly into boiling water. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cook 5 to 7 minutes or until grits begin to thicken. Stir in sandwich spread and eggs. Add 2 of the process cheese slices; stir until completely melted. Add garlic powder, salt and paprika. Pour into 9-inch square nonstick baking pan Bake at 350 degrees F for 45 minutes. Cut remaining 4 process cheese slices into small squares; arrange on top of grits. Bake an additional 3 minutes or until process cheese is melted. Cool 1 hour. Cut into 2-inch squares.